Bangladesh Football to Get Grant From FIFA
DHAKA , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- The Bangladesh Football Federation ( BFF ) will receive a grant of 250,000 U.S. dollars from the International Football Federation ( FIFA ) before the next World Cup Finals in 2002 .
The BFF would get the grant in five installments , with the first of 50,000 dollars within the next two months , the New Nation daily quoted BFF General Secretary Harun-ur-Rashid as saying on Sunday .
Rashid returned from Zurich , Switzerland on Friday after attending the FIFA media meeting on Wednesday .
FIFA President Joseph Blatter announced in France earlier this year that a part of FIFA 's earnings from the World Cup Finals would be given to support the least developed soccer-playing countries .
